                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; the names of the donor (or commissioner) and the copyst; the name of King Yoḥannǝs; elements of punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; abbreviations.&#xD;
The initial line on the incipit page of Text I (fol. 2r); two lines, alternating with a black line, in the incipit page of Text II (fol. 17v); incipit (1-3 words) of some subsections in Texts I and II (esp. fols. 3r, l.15, 5r, l.7, 11r, l.3, 14v, l.9, 15r, ls. 10-11, 18v, ls.15-16, 19v, ls.8-9, 20r, l.9, 21r, ls.10-11, 21v, ls.1 and 16, 22r, l.11, 23v, l.9, 28v, ls.15-16, 29v, ls.1-2 and 10, 30r, l.11, 30v, ls.8-9 and 16, 31r, l.10).</rubric>
                     <incipit defective="false">
                        <foreign xml:lang="en">(This is) the prayer of Incense in the peace to the Lord, the Father, the Son, Whom (They) sent and Who dwellt in the womb of the Virgin Saint Mary. Peace (is) from God and the Lord of all creatures.  There is no one who can count the glory of the Divinity.  </foreign>
                     </incipit>
